{
  "texts": [
    "We named the final set of 688 pairs the HOLO4K-AlphaFold2 Paired (HAP) set.",
    "We also extracted a set of 280 pairs which only contained proteins with lower than 25% sequence identity (calculated using Diamond [54]) to the P2Rank [17] training set (referred to as the HAP-small set).Our training set consists of structures taken from Binding MOAD [55][56][57].",
    "The Binding MOAD platform contains 11058 families (clusters) of proteins with each cluster containing a leader (the cluster centre) and members which each have over 90% sequence identity to the leader.",
    "We first removed any family for which the leader had greater than 25% sequence identity to any protein in our test set.",
    "For each of the remaining 6550 families, we aligned all members to the family leader, and labelled the residues of the leader as follows: any residues within 5Å of the ligand of the leader were labelled as binding residues; any remaining residue within 5Å of any ligand bound to member structures were not used in the dataset, to avoid the potential for false negative annotations; the remainder were labelled as non-binding."
  ]
}